reason: Alternate spelling, used by several dubs of the anime.
Same character, different spelling. It is written as "Nrvnqsr" and read as "Nero", so it could go any way.

Some people don't know that Vava was renamed to Vile in the US (and I think Euro) release.  "Vile" is ambiguous enough that it should never be a descriptor, and I can think of no other character, copyright, or artist that uses this.
We originally used the former, but then it changed and wasn't aliased.
